&quot;Helen Miller Gould was born in New York City, the eldest daughter of the famous financier, Jay Gould. She was educated by private instructors under the careful eye of her father. Perhaps Helen’s greatest work was her patriotic efforts during the Spanish-American War. To the United States Government at the outbreak of the war with Spain, she gave $100,000 for relief of the soldiers at Camp Wycoff, Long Island.&quot;
